@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "APIDocumentation";
}


<style>


    h1.display-4 {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: #2d2d2d;
    }

    h2 {
        color: #333;
        margin-top: 30px;
    }

    h3 {
        color: #2d2d2d;
        margin-top: 20px;
    }

    p, pre {
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: #555;
    }

    .api-endpoint {
        background-color: #f8f9fa;
        padding: 20px;
        border-radius: 8px;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    code {
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        background-color: #e9ecef;
        padding: 3px 8px;
        border-radius: 4px;
    }

    pre {
        background-color: #f8f9fa;
        border: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
        padding: 15px;
        border-radius: 8px;
        font-size: 1rem;
        white-space: pre-wrap;
        word-wrap: break-word;
    }



    img.img-fluid {
        max-width: 100%;
        height: auto;
    }

    @@media (max-width: 767px) {

        .row {
            flex-direction: column-reverse;
        }

        .col-md-7, .col-lg-7 {
            width: 100%;
        }

        .col-md-5, .col-lg-5 {
            width: 100%;
        }
    }

</style>
<div class="container mt-5">
    <div class="row align-items-center">
        <!-- Content Area (65-70%) -->
        <div class="col-md-7 col-lg-7">
            <h1 class="display-4">API Documentation</h1>
            <p class="lead">
                Welcome to the API documentation for **Apna AI**. This documentation provides details on how to interact
                with the AI backend, which can be integrated into your applications to leverage the capabilities of
                conversational AI for your needs.
            </p>
            <h2>Base URL</h2>
            <p>
                The base URL for accessing Apna AI API is:
                <code>https://api.apna-ai.com</code>
            </p>

            <h2>Endpoints</h2>
            <p>Below are the available API endpoints you can use to integrate with Apna AI:</p>

            <div class="api-endpoint">
                <h3>1. Query AI</h3>
                <p><strong>POST</strong> <code>/api/v1/query</code></p>
                <p>This endpoint allows you to send a query to Apna AI and receive a response. It supports natural language queries.</p>

                <h4>Example Request:</h4>
                <pre>
{
    "query": "What is the capital of France?"
}
                </pre>

                <h4>Example Response:</h4>
                <pre>
{
    "response": "The capital of France is Paris."
}
                </pre>
            </div>

            <div class="api-endpoint">
                <h3>2. Get Available Endpoints</h3>
                <p><strong>GET</strong> <code>/api/v1/endpoints</code></p>
                <p>Fetch a list of all available API endpoints and their descriptions.</p>

                <h4>Example Request:</h4>
                <pre>
GET /api/v1/endpoints
                </pre>

                <h4>Example Response:</h4>
                <pre>
{
    "endpoints": [
        {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "/api/v1/query",
            "description": "Submit a query to the AI."
        },
        {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "/api/v1/endpoints",
            "description": "Retrieve a list of all API endpoints."
        }
    ]
}
                </pre>
            </div>

            <div class="api-endpoint">
                <h3>3. Get AI Version</h3>
                <p><strong>GET</strong> <code>/api/v1/version</code></p>
                <p>Retrieve the current version of the Apna AI API.</p>

                <h4>Example Request:</h4>
                <pre>
GET /api/v1/version
                </pre>

                <h4>Example Response:</h4>
                <pre>
{
    "version": "1.0.0"
}
                </pre>
            </div>

            <h2>Authentication</h2>
            <p>All requests to the API require an API key, which can be obtained by registering on the Apna AI platform. Include your API key in the request header:</p>
            <pre>
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY
            </pre>
            <p>If you don't have an API key, you can request one by signing up on the Apna AI platform.</p>

            <h2>Error Handling</h2>
            <p>In case of an error, the API will return the following response format:</p>
            <pre>
{
    "error": "Invalid API key",
    "message": "The provided API key is invalid or expired."
}
            </pre>
        </div>

        <!-- SVG Image Area (30-35%) -->
        <div class="col-md-5 col-lg-5 text-center">
            <img src="~/images/apna-ai-api.svg" alt="API Icon" class="img-fluid" />
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


